Great post!

I wanted a bunch of houses and land. I would have been a landlord and charge rent.

But I am not a good candidate for such a life.

I already point out one way in this article I would be a bad candidate. My wife does not want to work. If she had to, she would, but I would simply hate living that way too. So my only choices are:

Wife. No. Kids will be years in the future. And those kids have a cold, frosty winter where their house would not have heating in November, for example. They would also not have proper appliances, nor would they move if they only fit one season. A family would be inconvenient in most cases. Also, what kind of quality would the houses be? It would be easier to build houses with kids, but my son would be miserable, and if the family or one person has a major issue about disability, perhaps they cannot live in Guatemala at all -- like if they were paraplegic or blind or quadriplegic.
